parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Pump Drive Belt Tensioner Arm Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil pump drive belt tensioner arm can cause a loss of engine oil pressure, leading to engine damage and seizure, which can result in a loss of motive power and a loss of the mechanical vacuum pump required to provide power braking assist, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The oil pressure light comes on
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine makes a loud noise
the vehicle is unable to be restarted
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle hesitates or stalls while driving
the engine oil pump malfunctioned.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Oil Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil pump can cause engine damage and seizure, leading to a loss of motive power and a loss of the mechanical vacuum pump required to provide power braking assist, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the oil pressure light comes on
the vehicle is unable to be restarted
the check engine light comes on
the engine makes a loud noise
the vehicle hesitates or stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The emissions system fault can cause exhaust and fuel fumes to leak into the cabin, leading to health problems for the occupants.
symptoms: Strong exhaust and fuel fumes inside the cabin
headaches
lethargy
nausea
and agitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure and Cooling System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and cooling system issues can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or overheat, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or engine damage.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or hesitates while accelerating; the check engine warning light
service engine soon light
or wrench symbol warning light is illuminated; white smoke is present coming from the exhaust system; the vehicle idles rough; the brake pedal is depressed
but the vehicle fails to brake as intended; the low oil pressure warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: The contact receives notification of a recall
but the part to do the recall repair is not yet available; the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or fail to respond, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to respond or hesitates while accelerating; the transmission fails to engage; the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system malfunction can cause the vehicle to fail to stop, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal is depressed
but the vehicle fails to brake as intended; the vehicle fails to stop before crashing into an object.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose acceleration, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Delayed transmission shifting
transmission slipping
loss of power
loud grinding sounds
inability to accelerate
sudden loss of power
and warning lights for powertrain failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Pressure and Performance Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine oil pressure and performance issues can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Low engine oil pressure notification
sudden loss of engine power
inability to accelerate
warning lights for engine oil pressure
and engine shutting off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Warning lights for anti-lock brakes
traction control
and other important driver assistance features
and electrical issues causing the vehicle to shut off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The axle and transmission seal failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud mechanical grinding sounds
transmission fluid leaking
and axle seal tearing.
